          'content': '<p>Currently, we live in an apartment that used to be a single family house and has since had a building built beneath it. I call it our Frakenhouse, it‚Äôs a monster of 1890‚Äôs and 1970‚Äôs architecture, but at least its rode out 2 major earthquakes, so it‚Äôs got that going for it. Our apartment is 2 stories, 3 bed, 1.5 bath, with lots of room to spare.</p><p>The plan is to sell just about everything (all furniture, a load of clothes, appliances, etc.). So far I‚Äôve been collecting and selling things piecemeal on facebook. We have a giant collection of boardgames that Justin has decided on half of which to sell. Currently I have 7 games I need to box up and mail to amazon so we can sell them on the amazon marketplace. I‚Äôm not complete in the process of selling things on amazon, but so far the process seems pretty easy. You sign up as a seller, upload your inventory (you can search and add to your inventory by UPC, which is fast and neat), decide on price, decide if you or amazon will fulfill the order. After you have created your inventory you create your shipment to amazon from your inventory, print labels, pack the box, and ship. I haven‚Äôt completely gone through the shipping to the amazon fulfillment center steps yet since it‚Äôs sunday, but plan to do that tomorrow or Tuesday when the library is open and I can use their printers. Once I‚Äôve tested out the selling process to the point of getting it out of my house, I‚Äôll probably be shipping 5-10 boxes to amazon, hopefully before christmas since it‚Äôs a major selling season ;)</p><p>Additionally, we‚Äôre trying to sell some of the smaller stuff on facebook in the various community groups set up for that sort of thing. I think when we‚Äôre closer to actually moving into the RV, we will have a do-it-yourself estate sale to sell furniture and whatnot. I‚Äôve barely started selling, but so far it seems to be a good way to go. Back up plan is to hire someone to sell the crap for us, or just donate it all.</p><p>To help me get my head in the game and plan this massive massive purge, I‚Äôve been reading up on tiny houses, lifestyle minimalists, home organizations tips. Pinterest has been a great help in finding me the resources to do such things. I‚Äôm still nervous about such a life change, but I‚Äôm excited to really live with just the things we need in just the right amount of space that we need.</p><p>As we keep downsizing, I‚Äôll post more information, in case there‚Äôs those who want to follow in our footsteps, so to speak.</p>'
